OL,3,CEstate agent wants new law to force
OL,4,Csellers to survey homes before sale
OL,6,FIn the UK, the average timeframe is
OL,7,Fabout four to six weeks, while it can
OL,8,Ftake up to three months in Guernsey.
OL,10,FThe process requires the purchaser to
OL,11,Fget a survey done on their prospective
OL,12,Fhome, which can be difficult due to a
OL,13,Flack of local surveyors, and may then
OL,14,Fidentify problems not previously known
OL,15,Fto either the buyer or the seller.
OL,17,FDepending on the extent of the issues,
OL,18,Fbanks may refuse to lend and the
OL,19,Fentire purchasing chain can collapse.
